The paper deals with trajectory planning for autonomous vehicles, which is a core problem in robotics (cs.RO). It also uses game theory to model the interactions between the autonomous vehicle and other drivers, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also introduces a novel algorithm for planning, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) or multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
